30/11/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Albanian Justice Minister Spiro Peci spoke in Brussels on Friday (28 November) about the Albanian government's latest measures aimed at fighting organised crime.
Addressing a conference of the EU and justice and interior ministers from the Western Balkans, Peci cited the approval of the law on creating the Heavy Crime Court, the amendments in penal legislation on money laundering and terrorism, and the law on protecting witnesses.
He stressed the importance of regional co-operation in regard to information exchange, joint police operations and judicial collaboration.
(ATA - 28/11/03)
